Farro, a variety of hulled wheat, is praised for its chewy texture and nutty flavor. To make this salad really shine, we paired the tasty ancient grain with spicy glazed honey roasted carrots and walnuts, sweet-tart marinated cranberries, lemony dressing, fresh kale, and a creamy herb dressing. This dinner is so good, it's almost not farro to the other grain bowls in the world.

== Farro ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a medium #pot over medium-high heat.
Add @farro{1/2%cup}. (Be sure to measure the farro; we sent more.) Cook,
stirring, until toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @water{3%cups}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of @salt{}.
Bring to boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. TIP: If you end
up with any excess liquid, simply pour it out. Alternatively, if liquid
evaporates before farro is done, add a splash more water.

== Carrots ==

While farro cooks, trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%oz} on a diagonal into
½-inch-thick pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{},
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack for ~{20%minutes} (you'll finish the carrots in step 5).

== Dressing ==

Meanwhile, zest and halve @lemon{1}. Pick @green herb blend{}(chopped) leaves
from stems; finely chop leaves. Finely chop chives. Remove and discard any
large stems from @chopped kale{4%oz}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces.

In a small #bowl, combine juice from half the lemon and @hot water{1%tbsp}.
Add @dried cranberries{1%oz} and set aside.

In a separate small bowl, whisk together @sour cream{4%tbsp},
@buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%oz}, chopped parsley, chives, a squeeze of lemon
juice, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of lemon zest to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a
time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper
to taste.

== Salad Assembly ==

Place kale in a large #bowl. Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{} and a squeeze of
remaining lemon juice; season lightly with @salt{}. Massage leaves until
tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> Don't skip this step—massaging helps the kale leaves wilt slightly, lending a
> tender (never fibrous!) texture.

Add drained farro and soaked cranberries (draining first). Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Add as much dressing as you like and toss to combine.

== Finish Carrots ==

Once carrots have roasted 20 minutes, carefully remove baking sheet from
#oven. Top with @honey{2%tsp}, @walnuts{1/2%oz}, and @chili flakes{1%tsp} to
taste. Carefully toss to coat.

Return to top rack until carrots are tender and glazed, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== To Serve ==

Divide farro and kale salad between plates or shallow bowls. Top with
honey-roasted carrots and walnuts. Serve.